snippet: Israeli pathologists say Ziad Abu Ein died of a heart attack, but a Palestinian forensic expert says Mr. Abu Ein died as a result of violence.
abstract: Israeli and Palestinian pathologists offer different interpretations of joint autopsy report on death of prominent Palestinian official Ziad Abu Ein, who died after confrontation with Israeli security forces at a West Bank demonstration; Israeli pathologists contend he died of heart attack caused by stress, while Palestinians hold that he died as result of violence and not from natural causes.

byline.original: By ISABEL KERSHNER and SAID GHAZALI
byline.contributor: Isabel Kershner reported from Jerusalem, and Said Ghazali from Ramallah, West Bank.

lead_paragraph: Israeli pathologists say Ziad Abu Ein died of a heart attack, but a Palestinian forensic expert says Mr. Abu Ein died as a result of violence.

headline.main: Doctors Draw Contradictory Conclusions After Autopsy of Palestinian Official
headline.print_headline: Doctors Draw Contradictory Conclusions After Autopsy of Palestinian Official
